    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6831/193: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-06T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 6, 1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 6—9:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Department’s instruction No. 445, March 8. The Prime Minister called me to
                    the Foreign Office this morning and read me a first person note, which he
                    subsequently handed me, accepting our proposal that we proceed immediately to
                    the negotiation of an accord incorporating the substance of the proposed <hi
                        rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> of July 19, 1937.<note n="19a"
                        xml:id="d419fn19a">See footnote 4, <ref target="#pg_517">p.
                        517</ref>.</note> I informed him that the Department is forwarding me a new
                    text embodying the same principles as that already proposed but more flexible in
                    certain respects. To this he replied that his Government remains at my
                    disposition, but I would be grateful if the Department would inform me as to the
                    probable date of arrival of the new text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
